# Notes

> This slide exists just temporarily to take notes during creation process. Don't remove or edit it unless explicitly asked :)

Problems:
- Creator wants create an educational & entertaining video of how he edited a Blender scene:
  - Look better than screen-recording / viewport-capture. No Blender UI.
  - Automatic removal of experimental & faulty steps.
  - Automatic positioning of camera.

Presentation Agenda (Idea & Plans):
- Motivation + Idea
- Similar existing plugins/tools/literature
- Concrete examples, outline envisioned end-to-end workflow/walkthrough, define target group
- Feasibility (outline how you plan to implement it)
- Roadmap (what do you plan to be done with by which point, esp. Milestone)
- Minimum viable product versus stretch goals
- Uncertainties: what is not fully decided yet? Present options/alternatives for parts where you might need support for your decision
- Questions to audience, about their experience, their thoughts?

+ Mögliche Erweiterungen, z.B. Action Inspector (vgl. Paintnet paper), Scene/Workflow Analysis (vgl. Dragon paper), Version-Tracking or Undo-Tree, Comparison-Lens, Timeline, Semantic-Diffing (Replay for specific components), Animations between Steps, Generation from File

---

# The Idea

- **Track** user actions in Blender in real-time
- **Record** viewport position, operators, scene mutations
- **Export** all data to a portable recording file
- **Replay:** open recording in a clean Blender project
- **Render** a timelapse video with:
  - Smooth camera animation (interpolated from viewport)
  - Every meaningful action as a rendered frame
  - Undone actions filtered out via undo-tree tracking

---

