# Recording Format: Open Question ⚡

<div class="grid grid-cols-[1fr_1fr] gap-4 mt-4">

<div class="p-3 rounded border border-gray/20">
  <div class="font-bold text-sm">A) File-based <span class="i-carbon:checkmark text-green inline-block align-middle ml-1" /></div>
  <div class="text-xs text-muted mt-2">
    Export recording to a<br/><code>.blend-recording/</code> directory
    <hr class="my-2" />
    Open in new Blender project →<br/>Add-on reconstructs scene + camera<br/>→ Render timelapse video
  </div>
  <div class="text-xs text-muted mt-1">✅ Clean separation · ✅ Reusable</div>
</div>

<div class="p-3 rounded border border-gray/20 op-50">
  <div class="font-bold text-sm">B) Same-scene scene</div>
  <div class="text-xs text-muted mt-2">
    Add timeline scene inside<br/>current project
    <hr class="my-1" />
    ❌ Clutters original project<br/>❌ May interfere with editing
  </div>
</div>

</div>

<div class="mt-4 p-3 rounded bg-yellow/10 border border-yellow/20 text-sm">
  <span class="i-carbon:idea inline-block align-middle mr-1" />
  <strong>My preference:</strong> File-based export → new Blender project → replay
</div>

---

# Render Approach: Open Question ⚡

<div class="grid grid-cols-[1fr_1fr] gap-4 mt-4">

<div class="p-3 rounded border border-gray/20">
  <div class="font-bold text-sm">Viewport Render</div>
  <div class="text-xs text-muted mt-2">
    <code>bpy.ops.render.opengl(write_still=True)</code>
  </div>
  <div class="text-xs text-muted mt-1">
    Captures what the user actually saw<br/>→ matches editing experience<br/>→ fast, no render engine needed
  </div>
</div>

<div class="p-3 rounded border border-gray/20">
  <div class="font-bold text-sm">Full Render</div>
  <div class="text-xs text-muted mt-2">
    Cycles / Eevee , final quality
  </div>
  <div class="text-xs text-muted mt-1">
    Each frame is a proper render<br/>→ beautiful but SLOW<br/>→ needs GPU time
  </div>
</div>

</div>

<div class="mt-4 p-3 rounded bg-blue/10 border border-blue/20 text-sm">
  <span class="i-carbon:idea inline-block align-middle mr-1" />
  <strong>Possible:</strong> Viewport render for preview / development, full render for final export
</div>

